<h1 class="mar-b-xs">Chip</h1>
<h2 class="txt-gray-5 mar-t-0">Used for filtering, triggering actions, prompts, and labeling information</h2>
<h2 id="demo">Demo</h2>
<code-sample>
<mw-chip kind="assist">
  <mw-icon name="event"></mw-icon>
  Assist
</mw-chip>
<mw-chip kind="filter">Filter</mw-chip>
<mw-chip kind="filter" aria-selected="true">Filter</mw-chip>
<mw-chip kind="input">
  Input
  <button type="remove"></button>
</mw-chip>
<mw-chip kind="suggestion">Suggestion</mw-chip>
</code-sample>
<h2 id="api">API</h2>
<h3 id="tag">Tag</h3>
<table layout="fixed">
  <thead>
  <tr>
    <th colspan="2">Name</th>
    <th colspan="2">Type</th>
    <th colspan="6">Content</th>
  </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><code>mw-chip</code></td>
    <td colspan="2">Custom tag</td>
    <td colspan="6">Text, icon, or link and optional remove button for <a href="#removable">removable chips</a></td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<h3 id="attributes">Attributes</h3>
<table layout="fixed">
  <thead>
  <tr>
    <th colspan="2">Name</th>
    <th colspan="2">Value</th>
    <th colspan="6">Description</th>
  </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><code>kind</code> <small class="fnt-bold fnt-italic">required</small></td>
    <td colspan="2">
      <ul type="none">
        <li>assist</li>
        <li>filter</li>
        <li>input</li>
        <li>suggestion</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
    <td colspan="6">
      <p>Defines the kind of chip it is. See <a href="https://m3.material.io/components/chips/guidelines" target="_blank">Material Chips</a> for complete details.</p>
      <p>Assist chips are similar to buttons and links, but their intended for triggering side-actions like adding an event to your device's calendar.</p>
      <p>Filter chips are very similar to checkboxes. Selecting them filters content.</p>
      <p>Input chips are added as input by the user and be removed by them, like the list of contacts when drafting a new message.</p>
      <p>Suggestion chips are simple words or phrases used to suggest some option, like search a prompt or auto-reply.</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><code>aria-selected</code> <small class="fnt-bold fnt-italic">filter kind only</small></td>
    <td colspan="2">
      <ul type="none">
        <li>true</li>
        <li>false</li>
      </ul>
    </td>
    <td colspan="6">
      <p>Sets filter chip selected state.</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
<h2 id="guidelines">Guidelines</h2>
<h3 id="removable">Removable chips</h3>
<p>Simply include a <a href="/button#remove">remove</a> button and, using your preferred method, attach a click handler that removes the chip. Here's a basic example:</p>
<code-sample>
  <script>
    const removeTag = (e, id) => confirm(`Remove "${id}" chip?`) ? e.target.parentElement.remove() : null;
  </script>
  <template>
    <mw-chip kind="input">bug<button type="remove" onclick="removeTag(event, 'bug')"></button></mw-chip>
    <mw-chip kind="input">open<button type="remove" onclick="removeTag(event, 'open')"></button></mw-chip>
    <mw-chip kind="input">high-priority<button type="remove" onclick="removeTag(event, 'high_pri')"></button></mw-chip>
  </template>
</code-sample>
